How to Install on Linux Machine

Prerequisites:
1. Package conky: sudo apt install conky

Steps:
1. Clone this repository: git clone https://github.com/bydzen/conky.git
2. Enter the directory: cd conky/
3. Create conky directory config and move main file: mkdir -p ~/.config/conky/ && mv bydzen.conkyrc ~/.config/conky/
4. Test & run the config file: conky -c "~/.config/conky/bydzen.conkyrc"

Autostart:
1. Create bash file: echo "sleep 5 && conky -c \"~/config/conky/bydzen.conkyrc\"" > ~/.config/conky/bydzen.conkyrc.sh
2. Make executable: chmod +x ~/.config/conky/bydzen.conkyrc.sh
3. Create autostart make sure target to the bash executable file.

More conky config documentation at https://conky.cc/

Enjoy.
